fields.description: A Transform can define more than one outputs. This property defines what the service should do when one output fails - either continue to produce other outputs, or, stop the other outputs. The overall Job state will not reflect failures of outputs that are specified with 'ContinueJob'. The default is 'StopProcessingJob'.
fields.name: OnError

fields.description: Preset that describes the operations that will be used to modify, transcode, or extract insights from the source file to generate the output.
fields.name: Preset

fields.description: Sets the relative priority of the TransformOutputs within a Transform. This sets the priority that the service uses for processing TransformOutputs. The default priority is Normal.
fields.name: RelativePriority
